race.comment: OUR COUVER (5) has switched from a Victorian yard on a 30-day return. Pushed forward from a wide draw last time leading for most of the way beaten 2L over 1406m at Benalla. That's good form and he will be tough to rein in. BOY BIG (3) proved too strong last start and scored by 3.5 lengths over 1200m in stronger. Has a 50% win record at the track and despite the weight lift he can go on with it. ALTAR BOY (2) turned in a decent effort making late ground to finish second to the above. Best figures measure up. EXPERT WITNESS (1) was in contention on the corner and was caught late in the same contest, well beaten in the end. Will trim down second-up and using the inside barrier can stick on better.
